<emphasis box="[323,446,1547,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. savignyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lucas" box="[454,585,1547,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Lucas, H. (1836) Observations sur les Araneides du genre Hersilia et description de deux especes nouvelles appartenant a ce genre. Magasin de Zoologie, 6 (8), 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1836">Lucas, 1836</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from related species by its rather short cymbium; tegular apophysis with a strongly projecting basal process and upper surface with pilose field on the latero-apical process (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,354,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,351,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Genitalia of H. savignyi Lucas, 1836. 5 left male palp (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.13), prolateral view; 6 same, ventral view; 7 same (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.15), retrolateral view; 8 epigyne (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.20), ventral view; 9 vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; LAP, latero-apical process of tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/546876/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[201,230,1616,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1623,1645]" captionTargetBox="[159,1418,153,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,147,1614]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Genitalia of H. savignyi Lucas, 1836. 10 left male palp, ventral view; 11 same, prolateral view; 12 epigyne, ventral view; 13 vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: CO, copulatory opening; E, embolus; LAP, latero-apical process of tegular apophysis; S, spermatheca. Scale bars: (10 – 13) 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/546877/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">10</figureCitation>
). The vulva is somewhat narrow and elongate with circular spermathecae; well sclerotized copulatory openings situated medially (
<figureCitation box="[348,451,1651,1674]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,354,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,351,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Genitalia of H. savignyi Lucas, 1836. 5 left male palp (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.13), prolateral view; 6 same, ventral view; 7 same (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.15), retrolateral view; 8 epigyne (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.20), ventral view; 9 vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; LAP, latero-apical process of tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/546876/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Figs. 8–9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[462,529,1651,1674]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1623,1645]" captionTargetBox="[159,1418,153,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,147,1614]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Genitalia of H. savignyi Lucas, 1836. 10 left male palp, ventral view; 11 same, prolateral view; 12 epigyne, ventral view; 13 vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: CO, copulatory opening; E, embolus; LAP, latero-apical process of tegular apophysis; S, spermatheca. Scale bars: (10 – 13) 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/546877/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">12–13</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Baehr" box="[551,783,1651,1674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Baehr, M. &amp; Baehr, B. (1993) The Hersiliidae of the Oriental Region including New Guinea. Taxonomy, phylogeny, zoogeography (Arachnida, Araneae). Spixiana, 19 (Supplement), 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr &amp; Baehr, 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1303,2021]" box="[199,1194,1685,1709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1686,1709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Description.</emphasis>
For detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Baehr" box="[644,883,1686,1709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Baehr, M. &amp; Baehr, B. (1993) The Hersiliidae of the Oriental Region including New Guinea. Taxonomy, phylogeny, zoogeography (Arachnida, Araneae). Spixiana, 19 (Supplement), 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr &amp; Baehr (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[935,1190,1685,1709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Pravalikha, G. B., Srinivasulu, C. &amp; Srinivasulu, B. (2014) New species of genus Hersilia Audouin, 1826 (Araneae: Hersiliidae) from India. Journal of Threatened Taxa, 6 (3), 5553 - 5557." type="journal article">
Pravalikha 
<emphasis box="[1056,1103,1685,1709]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1303,2021]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,279]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,505,1720,1743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Justification of synonymy.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[516,1014,1720,1743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Pravalikha, G. B., Srinivasulu, C. &amp; Srinivasulu, B. (2014) New species of genus Hersilia Audouin, 1826 (Araneae: Hersiliidae) from India. Journal of Threatened Taxa, 6 (3), 5553 - 5557." type="journal article">Pravalikha, Srinivasulu &amp; Srinivasulu (2014)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1223,1719,1744]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aadi">
<emphasis box="[1139,1223,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. aadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Osmania University campus, Hyderabad, (presently in Telengana state), India. The original description is based on 13 specimens (6♂ &amp; 7♀). 
<bibRefCitation box="[281,531,1789,1813]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Pravalikha, G. B., Srinivasulu, C. &amp; Srinivasulu, B. (2014) New species of genus Hersilia Audouin, 1826 (Araneae: Hersiliidae) from India. Journal of Threatened Taxa, 6 (3), 5553 - 5557." type="journal article">
Pravalikha 
<emphasis box="[401,447,1789,1813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
mention that 
<taxonomicName box="[677,756,1789,1813]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aadi">
<emphasis box="[677,756,1789,1813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. aadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1039,1790,1813]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[918,1039,1790,1813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group but do not provide any distinct diagnostic characters to distinguish between 
<taxonomicName box="[714,793,1823,1848]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aadi">
<emphasis box="[714,793,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. aadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[846,967,1824,1848]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[846,967,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, they provide good illustration of the epigyne and vulva which are clearly distinct and show no difference to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1219,1859,1882]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[1093,1219,1859,1882]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">H. savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. Image 3b-d in 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,407,1893,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Pravalikha, G. B., Srinivasulu, C. &amp; Srinivasulu, B. (2014) New species of genus Hersilia Audouin, 1826 (Araneae: Hersiliidae) from India. Journal of Threatened Taxa, 6 (3), 5553 - 5557." type="journal article">
Pravalikha 
<emphasis box="[273,321,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[462,562,1894,1917]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,354,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,351,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Genitalia of H. savignyi Lucas, 1836. 5 left male palp (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.13), prolateral view; 6 same, ventral view; 7 same (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.15), retrolateral view; 8 epigyne (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.20), ventral view; 9 vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; LAP, latero-apical process of tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/546876/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Figs. 8–9</figureCitation>
herein with fig. 22e-f in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baehr" box="[838,1082,1894,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Baehr, M. &amp; Baehr, B. (1993) The Hersiliidae of the Oriental Region including New Guinea. Taxonomy, phylogeny, zoogeography (Arachnida, Araneae). Spixiana, 19 (Supplement), 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr &amp; Baehr (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and figs. 
<quantity box="[1191,1261,1894,1917]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5559999999999996" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" unit="in" value="1.4">1, 4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Benoit" box="[1270,1432,1894,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Benoit, P. L. G. (1974) Araignees interessantes du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 81, 993 - 998. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 76056" type="journal article" year="1974">Benoit (1974))</bibRefCitation>
. Though the illustrations of the male palp is neither in a proper ventral nor retrolateral view the diagnostic characters such as the pilose latero-apical process of the tegular apophysis and embolus are however clearly evident (cf. Image 1i-j in 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,403,1997,2021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Pravalikha, G. B., Srinivasulu, C. &amp; Srinivasulu, B. (2014) New species of genus Hersilia Audouin, 1826 (Araneae: Hersiliidae) from India. Journal of Threatened Taxa, 6 (3), 5553 - 5557." type="journal article">
Pravalikha 
<emphasis box="[272,319,1997,2021]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[456,555,1998,2021]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,354,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,351,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Genitalia of H. savignyi Lucas, 1836. 5 left male palp (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.13), prolateral view; 6 same, ventral view; 7 same (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.15), retrolateral view; 8 epigyne (OUNHM. ART. ARA. 2011.20), ventral view; 9 vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; LAP, latero-apical process of tegular apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/546876/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Figs. 5–7</figureCitation>
with fig. 22c-d in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baehr" box="[755,1006,1998,2021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" refString="Baehr, M. &amp; Baehr, B. (1993) The Hersiliidae of the Oriental Region including New Guinea. Taxonomy, phylogeny, zoogeography (Arachnida, Araneae). Spixiana, 19 (Supplement), 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr &amp; Baehr (1993))</bibRefCitation>
. Examination of fresh material from the Madras Christian College campus and re-examination of the types of 
<taxonomicName box="[915,996,151,175]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aadi">
<emphasis box="[915,996,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">H. aadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1235,151,175]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aadi">
<emphasis box="[1154,1235,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">H. aadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indeed a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[284,405,186,209]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[284,405,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">H. savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="398" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[355,480,221,244]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[355,480,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">H. savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread species known to be distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[1095,1152,221,244]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1166,1275,221,244]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1315,1435,221,244]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="398">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(World Spider Catalog 2017).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
